choices.text:
I am not a prime number.
I am between 20 and 40.
I am one more than a square number.
What number am I?
The number is 36.
It can be derived by the following logic:
- The number cannot be a prime, so it must be greater than or equal to 2 (since all primes are less than or equal to 1).
- It also cannot be between 40 and 20, since that range does not include any square numbers.
- Therefore, the only possible options left are multiples of 36, which is one more than a square number (i.e., 9 x 4 = 36).
